Sentencas: The effects of Ca on the properties of PrBa1-xCaxCo2O5+delta (x = 0.0, 0.3, and 0.5) as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells were studied.
Titulo: Synergistic Effect of A-Site Cation Ordered-Disordered Perovskite as a Cathode Material for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Higher Ca content in PrBa1-xCaxCo2O5+delta led to a gradual change in phase symmetry from A-site cation ordered double perovskite (x = 0.0) to mixed A-site cation ordered-disordered perovskite (x = 0.3) to A-site cation disordered simple perovskite (x = 0.5).
Titulo: Synergistic Effect of A-Site Cation Ordered-Disordered Perovskite as a Cathode Material for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: It also led to a decreased oxygen content.
Titulo: Synergistic Effect of A-Site Cation Ordered-Disordered Perovskite as a Cathode Material for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Comparing the electrochemical performance of the samples with x = 0.0 and x = 0.5, PrBa0.7Ca0.3Co2O5+delta exhibited the best catalytic activity for the oxygen reduction reaction and maximum power density.
Titulo: Synergistic Effect of A-Site Cation Ordered-Disordered Perovskite as a Cathode Material for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This was ascribed to the synergistic effect of the A-site cation ordered-disordered structure, which combined the advantages of a fast oxygen diffusion rate and a relatively short oxygen diffusion distance from the oxygen reduction site to the cathode/electrolyte interface.
Titulo: Synergistic Effect of A-Site Cation Ordered-Disordered Perovskite as a Cathode Material for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density, which was as high as 2.16 W cm(-2), was achieved for the PrBa0.7Ca0.3Co2O5+delta-based single cell with a commercial anode-supported half cell at 800 degrees C. PrBa0.7Ca0.3Co2O5+delta was shown to be a potential cathode material for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Synergistic Effect of A-Site Cation Ordered-Disordered Perovskite as a Cathode Material for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
